AAPL Stock Price Time Series Analysis (2016–2026)

A statistical time series analysis of Apple Inc. (NASDAQ: AAPL) stock prices over a 10-year period using R. This project investigates trend behavior, stationarity, and autoregressive modeling on monthly aggregated stock prices.

This project was developed as part of the CIA-3 coursework for the B.Sc. Data Science & Artificial Intelligence program at Christ University Delhi NCR.

Project Overview

Financial time series such as stock prices are typically noisy, non-stationary, and influenced by external events. This project performs a structured statistical workflow to analyze the behavior of AAPL stock prices using classical time series techniques.

The study covers:

2,501 daily observations
Aggregated into 120 monthly data points
Analysis period: April 2016 – March 2026

The workflow includes:

Data preprocessing
Trend analysis using moving averages
Stationarity diagnostics
Log transformation and differencing
Linear regression modelling
Autoregressive modelling
Objectives
Data Acquisition & Preprocessing
Load AAPL daily price data, convert date format, filter the last 10 years of observations, and aggregate daily prices into monthly averages.
Trend Analysis
Identify price trends using Simple Moving Average (SMA) and Exponential Moving Average (EMA) with windows of 3, 6, and 12 months.
Stationarity Assessment
Evaluate whether the time series is stationary using ACF, PACF, block mean analysis, and block variance analysis.
Transformation to Stationarity
Apply log transformation and first-order differencing to stabilize the series.
Model Fitting
Fit statistical models including Linear Regression, AR(1), and AR(2).
Dataset

The dataset consists of daily Apple Inc. stock prices.

Features include:

Date
Open
High
Low
Close
Volume

The data is filtered to retain the most recent 10 years of trading history and aggregated into monthly mean closing prices.

